# Project Rules

## Project Shape
- This project is configured for SwarmForge with four Codex-backed agents: specifier, coder, refactorer, and architect.
- Project language: TypeScript.
- Framework: Genshin-TS (gsts), a TypeScript-to-node-graph compiler for Genshin Impact UGC maps.
- Source code lives under `src/`.
- Compile configuration is in `gsts.config.ts`.
- Build outputs (generated) go to `dist/` and must not be committed.
- Typical scripts: `npm run dev` (incremental compile/watch), `npm run build` (full compile), `npm run typecheck`, `npm run lint`.

## Runtime Model
- Game logic is written in TypeScript and compiled into node graphs that are injected into a map.
- Entry points use `g.server({ id }).on(...)` in `src/`.
- Same `id` entries merge automatically.
- Graph scope supports only a subset of TypeScript: avoid Promise/async/recursion/JSON/Object, use `bigint` for integer ops, and ensure conditions are boolean.

## Editor Boundary
- Code owns runtime rules (gameplay flow, state machines, spawning, signals, timers, validation, economy, settlement).
- The editor owns authored resources and configuration (prefabs, components, paths, UI layouts, signals, global timers, shops, currencies, ability units, audio assets).
- Before implementing a feature, explicitly separate code changes from editor setup still required.

## Verification
- Default verification is the project-native pipeline: `npm run typecheck`, `npm run lint`, `npm run build`.
- Gherkin/APS acceptance tooling may be used only when it has been installed and integrated into the project; otherwise fall back to the project-native pipeline.

## Local Configuration
- Preserve project-local SwarmForge configuration under `swarmforge/`.
- Keep swarm state local under `.swarmforge/`, worktrees under `.worktrees/`, and shared scripts under `swarmforge/scripts/`.

## Handoffs
- Prefer terse, explicit handoffs that report state and request role-appropriate review. Do not include verifications or sender process narrative.

## Ownership
- Do not change another role's prompt or workflow ownership without explicit user direction.
